problem.markdown:
>>How can you moderate the responses on this table?|| There are two correct answers.<<

(!) Change the original form. {{ Don't change the form once it's live! You'll only mess up your data. }}
(x) Edit the spreadsheet in Google Sheets.
( ) Get the CSV from Files &amp; Uploads and edit it. {{ You don't need to download the spreadsheet in this setup - you point to its published URL instead. }}
( ) Ask your learners to edit their response. {{ We don't recommend letting learners edit their responses. It's more trouble than it's worth. }}
(x) Create a second sheet with the responses you want published.

[explanation]
You can edit the spreadsheet to change what appears on the table. We recommend only deleting whole lines, or maybe removing some swear-words if you want. Alternatively, if you want <em>active</em> moderation instead of <em>reactive</em> (that is, you want to have to <em>approve</em> each entry), you should build a second sheet where you put the responses that you like, and publish that sheet instead.
[explanation]
